[h1]Features[/h1]
[h2]Wonders[/h2]
[b]Space Elevator[/b]
- Adds Clerks and Merchants (or Logistics Drones) and many different bonuses.

[b]Research Wonders:[/b] Each is [b]Empire Unique[/b]. Complete Special Event Chains to [b]upgrade[/b] them.
- [b]Particle Supercollider[/b] -> [b]Interdimensional Collider[/b];
- [b]Domed City[/b] -> [b]Psionic Observatory[/b];
- [b]Abyssal Test Crater[/b] -> [b]Metal Vivarium[/b];

[b]Astronomical Model Bureau[/b] ([b]Empire Unique[/b])
- Bureaucrats, Administrators and more administration bonuses.
- Complete the event chain to upgrade to [b]Aligned Galactic Model[/b].

[b]Enigma Engine[/b] (For Machine Empires, requires Synthetic Dawn)
- [b]Empire Unique[/b] and only on Machine Worlds.
- Adds Enigma Operators, that produce research and unity.
- Unlocks new mysterious Enigma Technology.

[b]Solipsist Debate Hall[/b] (For Hive Minds, requires Utopia)
- [b]Empire Unique[/b] and only on Hive Worlds.
- Adds a variety of jobs per pop.
- Allows for Debates Events where [strike]I pretend to understand philosophy[/strike] the empire gains bonuses as the gestalt debates with itself or plays chess.

[b]Guardian Angel[/b]
- Adds Soldiers and Enforcers.
- Creates a Flying Fortress army to defend the planet.
- Special features for times of peace.
- Upgrades to [b]Stellar Sentinel[/b].

[b]Resource Wonders:[/b]
- [b]Erebus Project[/b] -> [b]Erebus Fracking Plant[/b]
- [b]Helios Tower[/b] -> [b]Helios Translucer Obelisk[/b]
- [b]Demetrius Cornucopia[/b] -> [b]Demetrius Chemical Garden[/b]

- Each adds Miners, Technicians and Farmers respectively and boosts those jobs.
- Each upgrade is [b]Empire Unique[/b] and adds jobs that produce rare resources.

[b]Mantle Crucible[/b]
- Adds Metallurgists and Artisans.
- [u]Decreases habitability[/u], increases alloy and consumer goods production.
- Can upgrade to [b]Titan Forge[/b] which is [b]Empire Unique[/b], provides only Metallurgists and unlocks the War Titan army.
- OR can upgrade to [b]Industrial Hearth[/b] which is [b]Empire Unique[/b], provides new Poly-Artisan jobs (that produce consumer goods and unity) and unlocks special technologies.

[b]Pavilion of Wonders[/b]
- Adds Entertainers and Culture Workers.
- Unlocks decision to host art exhibitions across the empire (even more with the Mega Art Installation Megastructure).
- Can upgrade to [b]Fair of Worlds[/b] which is [b]Empire Unique[/b] and only for [b]Xenophiles[/b], improves the exhibitions and unlocks a campaign.
- OR can upgrade to [b]Museum of the Grotesque[/b] which is [b]Empire Unique[/b] and only for [b]Xenophobes[/b], improves the exhibitions and unlocks a campaign.

[b]Holy Reliquary[/b] (Spiritualists only)
- Adds Priests (and a Relic Keeper when all artifacts are sanctified).
- Unlocks an edict and a decision to access the Reliquary, a new menu to sanctify 7 artifacts corresponding to each (base) tradition.
- Each Artifact has unique modifiers that can be changed at any time.
- Sanctify artifacts by spending Unity, change modifiers by spending Influence.

[b]The Grand Archive[/b] (Materialists only)
- Adds Grand-Archivists (and a Master Archivist when all collections are assembled).
- Unlocks an edict and a decision to access the Archive, a new menu to assemble 9 collections corresponding to each research field.
- Each Collection adds a Planetary Deposit that boosts research and unlocks unique techs.
- Assemble collections by spending Unity and completing special projects, unlock their techs by spending Influence.

[b]Transplanetary Logistics Network[/b] (Egalitarian only)
- Unlocks decision to improve infrastructure (Planetary Features).
- There are 4 types of infrastructure and each has 4 levels.
- The last level requires a specific Wonder in that planet (like Guardian Angel for Crisis Responders).

[b]Forbidden City[/b] (Authoritarian only)
- Unlocks decision to improve infrastructure (Planetary Features).
- There are 3 types of infrastructure and each has 4 levels, but one is only available on the capital.
- Each ethic has its own infrastructure too.

[b]Festival Plaza[/b] (Pacifist only)
- Unlocks decisions to make Peace Festivals.
- Each Peace Festival increases the rank of a Peace Stability country modifier.
- All modifiers/festivals are suspended during wars.

[b]Martial Avenue[/b] (Militarist only)
- Unlocks decisions to make Martial Parades.
- Each Martial Parades increases the rank of a War Drive country modifier.
- War Drive can cause debuffs if too high, but turns into War Lust (no debuffs) during wars.

[b]Department of Xenoeconomics[/b] (Megacorps only)
- Increases trade value and branch office value.
- Unlocks unique Branch Office Buildings that exploit other countries ethics in the name of profit.
- New Branch Office Buildings are planet-unique and restricted to 1 on each foreign empire.

[b]Panopticon[/b]
- For Penal Colonies (or Police State empires).
- Unlocks the Panspectron edict.

[b]Blossoming Preserve[/b]
- For Gaia and Hive Wolds.
- Unlocks the Harmonious Blossom edict.

[b]Nostalgia Paradise[/b]
- For Resort Worlds and Rogue Servitors.
- Choose a theme for the resort.

[b]Unhallowed Necropolis[/b]
- For Tomb/Relic Wolds and Necro empires.
- Allows the designation of Mausoleum Worlds.

[b]Feasting Grounds[/b]
- For Devouring Swarm/Terravore empires.
- Allows a decision to start banquets, that when completed give bonuses.

[b]Living Spire[/b] (Unlocked by AP - for Regular Empires)
- Has 4 stages that gives bonuses to housing, growth and amenities.
- Adopts a designation when concluded.

[b]Conduit of Unity[/b] (Unlocked by AP - for Gestalts Empires)
- Has 2 stages and unlocks Decision to build Planetary Deposits.
- Planetary Deposits represent Integrated Infrastructures for the Gestalt.
[h2]Additional Content[/h2]
- Ascension Perk: [b]"Planetary Wonders"[/b]
Allows for multiple Wonders per planet.
Unlocks the Living Spire (Regular Empires) or the Conduit of Unity (Gestalt Empires);

- New Tradition: [b]"Monumentality"[/b]: Improves buildings, Wonders and Megastructures.

- Edict: [b]"Wonders Beyond Ambition"[/b] (Unlocked by finishing Monumentality)
